Instructions
- Use the `OrderList` component from `src/components/orders/OrderList.tsx` to render the main data grid.
- Implement a `useOrders` custom hook or utilize a library like SWR/React Query to manage the GET request to `/api/orders` with the specified query parameters (status, start_date, end_date, user_id, page, limit).
- Map the API response (OrderListResponse) to the component state, ensuring `totalCount` and `hasNextPage` are used to drive the pagination UI.
- Create a filter form using controlled components that updates the URL search parameters on submission or change.
- Implement a status badge mapping that translates backend status strings (pending, processing, shipped, delivered) into theme-consistent UI colors.
